SKILL|design-md|Author/validate/export Google's DESIGN.md token spec files.
STEP|1|**YAML front matter** — machine-readable design tokens (normative values)
STEP|2|**Markdown body** — human-readable rationale, organized into canonical sections
STEP|3|User asks for a DESIGN.md file, design tokens, or a design system spec
STEP|4|User wants consistent UI/brand across multiple projects or tools
STEP|5|User pastes an existing DESIGN.md and asks to lint, diff, export, or extend it
STEP|6|User asks to port a style guide into a format agents can consume
STEP|7|User wants contrast / WCAG accessibility validation on their color palette
STEP|8|**Primary (#1A1C1E):** Deep ink for headlines and core text.
STEP|9|**Tertiary (#B8422E):** "Boston Clay" — the sole driver for interaction.
STEP|10|Overview (alias: Brand & Style)
STEP|11|Colors
STEP|12|Typography
STEP|13|Layout (alias: Layout & Spacing)
STEP|14|Elevation & Depth (alias: Elevation)
STEP|15|Shapes
STEP|16|Components
STEP|17|Do's and Don'ts
STEP|18|**Ask the user** (or infer) the brand tone, accent color, and typography
STEP|19|**Write `DESIGN.md`** in their project root using `write_file`. Always
STEP|20|**Use token references** (`{colors.primary}`) in the `components:` section
STEP|21|**Lint it** (see below). Fix any broken references or WCAG failures
STEP|22|**If the user has an existing project**, also write Tailwind or DTCG
STEP|23|`broken-ref` (error) — `{colors.missing}` points at a non-existent token
STEP|24|`duplicate-section` (error) — same `## Heading` appears twice
STEP|25|`invalid-color`, `invalid-dimension`, `invalid-typography` (error)
STEP|26|`wcag-contrast` (warning/info) — component `textColor` vs `backgroundColor`
STEP|27|`unknown-component-property` (warning) — outside the whitelist above
STEP|28|**Don't nest component variants.** `button-primary.hover` is wrong;
STEP|29|**Hex colors must be quoted strings.** YAML will otherwise choke on `#` or
STEP|30|**Negative dimensions need quotes too.** `letterSpacing: -0.02em` parses as
STEP|31|**Section order is enforced.** If the user gives you prose in a random order,
STEP|32|**`version: alpha` is the current spec version** (as of Apr 2026). The spec
STEP|33|**Token references resolve by dotted path.** `{colors.primary}` works;
STEP|34|Repo: https://github.com/google-labs-code/design.md (Apache-2.0)
STEP|35|CLI: `@google/design.md` on npm
STEP|36|License of generated DESIGN.md files: whatever the user's project uses;
